#   DIS-028: `?main` against a git remote fails WIRECLFL ‚Äî trunk‚áîrefs/heads/main alias eats the literal branch

be's wire layer aliases be-side trunk (empty branch `""`) to git's default `refs/heads/main` (`keeper/WIRECLI.c:304-324`). The collapse is one-directional-blind: `wcli_wire_to_be` maps a fetched `refs/heads/main` entry to be-side EMPTY (trunk), so when a user asks EXPLICITLY for `?main` (`want_branch = "main"`, non-empty) the peer's `refs/heads/main` is recorded as trunk and never matches the literal want ‚Üí no ref found ‚Üí `fatal: the remote end hung up unexpectedly` / `WIRECLFL`. Every other branch name works (`?master`, `?feat/x`); only the literal `main` is unsatisfiable. This is the read-only `WIRECLFL` first seen on `be head ssh://localhost/src/dogs/abc?main` (DIS-026 Issues) and is independent of the DIS-026 push fix. The goal: an explicit `?main` resolves the peer's `refs/heads/main` like any other name, while the bare-trunk (`""`) alias keeps working. See [DIS-026], [POST].

##  Issues
The trunk‚áîmain alias cannot tell "trunk requested (empty)" from "main requested literally".

 -  `wcli_be_to_wire`/`wcli_wire_to_be` (`keeper/WIRECLI.c:304-324`): `""` ‚áî `refs/heads/main`; the wire‚Üíbe direction collapses `refs/heads/main` to empty unconditionally (`:468-491`, the "refs/heads/main ‚Äî be's canonical trunk wire alias" branch).
 -  Ref-match (`wcli_*` matcher ~`:375-491`): with `want_branch = "main"`, the fetched `refs/heads/main` becomes be-side empty, so it fails to match the non-empty want ‚Üí fetch finds nothing ‚Üí WIRECLFL.
 -  Repro: `be head ssh://peer?master` ‚Üí OK (ahead/behind); `be head ssh://peer?main` ‚Üí `the remote end hung up unexpectedly` / `WIRECLFL`, against the SAME peer.
 -  Read-only path ‚Äî a `be head` dry-run should never fail to resolve a ref the peer plainly advertises.

##  Blockers
None. Mostly disjoint from the landed DIS-026 (sniff) / DIS-027 (`keeper/WIRECLI.c` push `wpush_*`); this is the FETCH/ref-mapping region of the same file ‚Äî keep the change localized.

##  Planned
Make `?main` resolve the peer's literal `refs/heads/main`; keep the bare-trunk alias intact.

 -  Repro first ([CLAUDE] ¬ß17): a hermetic BARE git peer with `refs/heads/main` at a tip (and a `master` at the same tip to show the contrast); assert `be head ssh://peer?main` resolves it (ahead/behind, exit 0) ‚Äî FAILS with WIRECLFL pre-fix ‚Äî while `be head ssh://peer?master` already works, and bare-trunk `be get ssh://peer` (no `?ref`) still maps to `refs/heads/main`.
 -  Trace `keeper/WIRECLI.c` wire‚Üîbe mapping (`:304-324`, `:449-491`): the collapse of `refs/heads/main`‚Üíempty must fire ONLY when the caller wants trunk (empty `want_branch`), NOT when `want_branch` is the literal `"main"`. Resolve the explicit `main` to be-side `"main"` and match `refs/heads/main` to it.
 -  Verify no regression to the bare-trunk alias (empty want still picks up `refs/heads/main`) and to push (`wpush_*`, DIS-027) ‚Äî run the full ssh suite.
 -  Regression test under `test/` (a `get`/`head` case): `?main` against a peer resolves; bare-trunk still maps to `refs/heads/main`; register + INDEX.md.

